hpnicfVrrpExt.name: hpnicfVrrpExt
hpnicfVrrpExt.description: This MIB describes objects used for managing Virtual Router Redundancy Protocol (VRRP) routers.

hpnicfVrrpExtTable.name: hpnicfVrrpExtTable
hpnicfVrrpExtTable.description: Table extends for a VRRP router which consists of a sequence (i.e., one or more conceptual rows) of hpnicfVrrpExtEntry items.

hpnicfVrrpExtEntry.name: hpnicfVrrpExtEntry
hpnicfVrrpExtEntry.description: An entry in the hpnicfVrrpExtTable containing the status values of a virtual router.

hpnicfVrrpExtTrackInterface.name: hpnicfVrrpExtTrackInterface
hpnicfVrrpExtTrackInterface.description: This value is the ifIndex that identifies which interface the virtual router tracked.

hpnicfVrrpExtPriorityReduce.name: hpnicfVrrpExtPriorityReduce
hpnicfVrrpExtPriorityReduce.description: This value identifies how much priority of a virtual router will be reduced/increased when the interface tracked is down/up.

hpnicfVrrpExtRowStatus.name: hpnicfVrrpExtRowStatus
hpnicfVrrpExtRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. Setting this object to active(1) or createAndGo(4) results in the addition of the ifIndex tracked by a virtual router. Destroying the entry removes the tracked ifIndex from the virtual router. Other values is not supported now.
